<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Semantic Tags - Time</title>
</head>
<body>
    <section>
        <h1>
            The &lt;time&gt; Element Showcase
        </h1>
        <h3>
            Examples of the &lt;time&gt; Element
        </h3>
        <h4>
            Date Only (YYYY-MM-DD)
        </h4>
        <p>
            The following is a date: <time datetime="YYYY-MM-DD">January 1, 2023</time>.
        </p>
        <h4>
            Time Only (24-Hour Format)
        </h4>
        <p>
            The following is a time: <time datetime="24-Hour">13:45 (1:45 PM)</time>.
        </p>
        <h4>
            Date and Time Combination
        </h4>
        <p>
            The following is a date and time: <time datetime="Time Combination">January 1, 2023, at 13:45</time>.
        </p>
        <h4>
            Datetime with Timezone
        </h4>
        <p>
            The following is a datetime with a timezone: <time datetime="Timezone">January 1, 2023, at 13:45 UTC</time>.
        </p>
        <h4>
            Human-readable Date with Datetime Attribute
        </h4>
        <p>
            The following is a human-readable date: <time datetime="Date with Datetime Attribute">New Year's Day 2023</time>.
        </p>
    </section>

</body>
</html>
